author: USA TODAY, Rebecca Morin, USA TODAY
title: Wisconsin's messy primary could foretell a messier run up to the November election in the coronavirus era
description: Wisconsin is the first state to hold a primary when much of the country is under stay-at-home orders – including the Badger State – amid the coronavirus pandemic.
content:
Milwaukee mayoral candidate state Sen. Lena Taylor, wearing a mask, had harsh words for state and local leaders at Riverside High School, one of the five polling places open in Milwaukee on April 7.
